{{Otheruses|Oseon}}
The '''Flamewind of Oseon''' was a [[Death|deadly]] wave of [[radiation]] originating in a [[star system]] in [[the galaxy]].<ref name="StarshipsSpeeders">''[[Starships and Speeders]]''</ref> It shared its name with the [[Oseon system]].<ref name="Lando">{{EncyclopediaCite|Lando Calrissian and Other Characters From the Galaxy}}</ref>

{{RPGseed}}
During the [[Imperial Era]], the [[smuggler]] [[Landonis Balthazar Calrissian|Lando Calrissian]] invited a group of travelers on a smuggling run with him on the [[YT-1300 light freighter]] ''[[Millennium Falcon]]'', for which they would receive their share in a massive payout after surviving the Flamewind of Oseon.<ref name="StarshipsSpeeders" />
{{Endgame}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Flamewind of Oseon was mentioned in the current ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] in ''[[Starships and Speeders]]'', a [[2020]] supplement to [[Fantasy Flight Games]]' ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying]]'' game.<ref name="StarshipsSpeeders" /> The [[Flamewind of Oseon/Legends|Flamewind of Oseon]] originated in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity in ''[[Lando Calrissian and the Flamewind of Oseon]]'', a [[1983]] novel written by [[L. Neil Smith]] as the second volume in the ''[[Star Wars: The Lando Calrissian Adventures]]'' trilogy. It was visually depicted in an [[:File:Flamewind of Oseon Cover.jpg|illustration]] by [[William Schmidt]] on the novel's original cover.<ref name="Flamewind">''[[Lando Calrissian and the Flamewind of Oseon]]''</ref>

